478
00:39:54,558 --> 00:39:56,560
I'd staple your lips
if you weren't my mom.

479
00:39:59,355 --> 00:40:00,731
Just say it, okay?

480
00:40:01,440 --> 00:40:05,319
Honk, honk, honk!

481
00:40:05,403 --> 00:40:07,196
Honk, honk, honk!

482
00:40:08,447 --> 00:40:09,824
Have you lost your mind?

483
00:40:10,950 --> 00:40:12,034
OK PSYCHIATRIC HOSPITAL

484
00:40:12,118 --> 00:40:12,952
Sir.

485
00:40:14,078 --> 00:40:15,871
What is your name?

486
00:40:18,624 --> 00:40:20,501
Do you know where you are now?

487
00:40:24,463 --> 00:40:25,714
This is odd.

488
00:40:27,633 --> 00:40:29,635
His condition can change suddenly,

489
00:40:30,136 --> 00:40:31,929
so keep an eye on him and update me.

490
00:40:32,012 --> 00:40:32,847
Yes, sir.

491
00:40:36,976 --> 00:40:37,893
Where have you been?

492
00:40:38,769 --> 00:40:41,689
I was feeling a little stuffy
so I went for a walk.

493
00:40:42,648 --> 00:40:43,482
Last week...

494
00:40:43,566 --> 00:40:44,400
Ko...

495
00:40:45,860 --> 00:40:47,736
Dae-hwan.

496
00:40:50,990 --> 00:40:52,199
What did you say?

497
00:40:54,243 --> 00:40:55,244
She's

498
00:40:56,954 --> 00:40:58,664
so beautiful.

499
00:41:00,666 --> 00:41:01,500
She looks

500
00:41:02,918 --> 00:41:05,921
like an angel.

501
00:41:09,008 --> 00:41:10,509
Who looks like an angel?

502
00:41:20,060 --> 00:41:21,729
Mun-yeong's...

503
00:41:23,939 --> 00:41:25,024
mother.

504
00:41:31,530 --> 00:41:33,699
You shouldn't be drinking.

505
00:41:33,949 --> 00:41:35,034
I didn't drink.

506
00:41:44,793 --> 00:41:48,214
It's probably too soon
for another one-on-one with Ms. Ko, right?

507
00:41:48,881 --> 00:41:51,800
You know what happened last time
they went out for a walk.

508
00:41:52,426 --> 00:41:54,470
But are you sure
he did that to his daughter?

509
00:41:55,429 --> 00:41:56,472
What do you mean?

510
00:41:59,683 --> 00:42:02,853
It's possible that he saw someone else
when he was looking at her.

511
00:42:05,397 --> 00:42:06,607
Who?

512
00:42:07,274 --> 00:42:08,317
We have to find out.

513
00:42:09,485 --> 00:42:12,279
Your snitch didn't tell you
anything about that?

514
00:42:13,364 --> 00:42:15,533
I'll keep the linen room locked
from now on.

515
00:42:19,370 --> 00:42:20,621
She knows everything.

516
00:42:35,469 --> 00:42:36,637
I slept so well.

517
00:43:01,829 --> 00:43:04,164
Ms. Ko, did you sleep well?

518
00:43:04,248 --> 00:43:05,082
Oh, yes.

519
00:43:11,547 --> 00:43:13,841
We got up at 6 a.m.
We washed all the sheets,

520
00:43:13,924 --> 00:43:16,385
picked up groceries, and cleaned

521
00:43:16,468 --> 00:43:18,679
while you slept.

522
00:43:30,649 --> 00:43:31,483
Come and eat.

523
00:43:32,192 --> 00:43:33,569
Sang-tae, go wash your hands.

524
00:43:35,696 --> 00:43:37,656
Hands should be washed in the bathroom.

525
00:43:43,912 --> 00:43:47,499
What do you have for breakfast?
We usually just have rice for breakfast.

526
00:43:50,044 --> 00:43:51,045
Do you prefer bread?

527
00:43:52,546 --> 00:43:53,756
No, rice.

528
00:43:54,256 --> 00:43:55,090
Okay.

529
00:44:08,062 --> 00:44:09,063
